      "span_text": "While most exacerbations are due to viral or bacterial infections, up to one-third have an unknown aetiology There is an abundance of literature, which implicates abnormalities of the cardiovascular system as an important factor in the prognosis of patients with COPD. Recent research has suggested that there may be greater overlap between the pathophysiology of the lungs and the heart than was previously appreciated."
